      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "Constraint-Manifold Projection and Target Discrepancy Evaluation. Maps a target in observation space to a candidate in latent state space using an inverse constraint solver, while also projecting an initial latent-state guess onto a feasible constraint manifold. In parallel, computes a non-negative squared Euclidean discrepancy between a current observation vector and a goal observation vector. The result is a feasibility-adjusted initialization, an inverse-mapped candidate state, and a scalar objective component for downstream optimization or ranking.. Applications: Computational chemistry: project a molecular conformation seed onto valid geometric constraints and infer a conformation that matches target descriptor coordinates., Computer graphics/animation: recover rig control parameters that produce a target marker layout while tracking squared discrepancy to a desired pose trajectory., Medical imaging: estimate latent deformation parameters that align anatomy landmarks to target coordinates and compute residual alignment error., Wireless localization: infer latent source/environment parameters from desired measurement-space targets and evaluate squared position mismatch to a navigation goal.",
