      "conceptual_summary": "Local Flow and Sensitivity Linearization Operator. Given a point in a continuous state space, a concurrent conditioning vector, and a scalar index, this operation evaluates the instantaneous velocity field at that point. It then computes the first-order Jacobian of that velocity map to produce a tangent-space linear approximation of nearby evolution. The pair captures both immediate directional change and local sensitivity of that change to perturbations.. Applications: Perturbation and stability analysis of biochemical reaction-network kinetics, Small-signal linearization of electromechanical grid and converter dynamics, Local forecast-sensitivity operators for geophysical fluid data assimilation, Real-time tangent models for deformable-body simulation and control in graphics/robotics",
